{"recommendationid": "14153686", "author": {"steamid": "76561197983295555", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 3, "playtime_forever": 2518, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1603, "last_played": 1474677126}, "language": "english", "review": "short answer: This is to FarCry3 as the Shivering Isles was to Oblivion. This is a new map with literally everything except the storyline the same. It's DLC and should be $20

Sligtly elaborated:
You could buy FarCry 3 and you wouldn't know the difference except the storyline getting much worse in 4. You're here to spread your mother's ashes, and immediately become a ruthless killer, stabbing anyone in your way with a machete? The guns and animations are exactly the same, the graphics are about the same, concept is the exact same (liberate towers, kill everyone in an outpost before they sound the alarm, random enemies driving around until you liberate the area). Seriously, it is the exact same game minus the main missions but including side missions. The devs were incredibly lazy with the copy+pasting.", "timestamp_created": 1422148252, "timestamp_updated": 1422148252, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "14121363", "author": {"steamid": "76561197971116017", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 42, "playtime_forever": 3576, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2839, "last_played": 1431575056}, "language": "english", "review": "So just to perfectly clear this review will have spoilers.







Well I just finished the game and I have to say the ending actually made me feel sick to my stomach.  Let me explain.  Sabal and Amita I did not like either one of them and I kinda wish that Ajay could have made his own choice and not followed either one of those two.  They were polar opposites but both of them were douche bags for real.  Pagan Min is awesome though his whole character the part he played in your life, your moms, and dads was actually really important I wanted to join his side once I found out everything that was going on.  I would have loved the choice to join him in the game and go kill Amita and Sabal.  Once you get to the end and find out what was going on I feel so very sorry for Pagan Min not that he would want Ajays sympathy.

At the very end when he gets on the helicopter and starts to fly away I blew it up and it actually made me feel nauseated when the horn blew and the words on the screen said THE KING IS DEAD.  There is I feel a deep and meaningful story here in this game but it makes you work to find and understand it.  I am not saying Pagan was innocent I am just saying i think in the end he was a lesser of the evils.", "timestamp_created": 1421987612, "timestamp_updated": 1421987612, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "14118551", "author": {"steamid": "76561198085946143", "num_games_owned": 1159, "num_reviews": 76, "playtime_forever": 2088, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2079, "last_played": 1427315902}, "language": "english", "review": "Far Cry 4, Feels like Far Cry 3, Which is great.

The fourth installment in an excellent game line takes you to Kyrat, In search for the location to place your mother's ashes. Along the way you run into the "villian" Pagan min, whom you just can't prevent loving. He takes on a lot of characteristics of Vaas from #3, which became infamous among the gaming community. Min, The flamboyant Villian, Hates everyone but you. You're special to him. Why? Find out yourself. You can't pass by this game. 

You can fight through the whole country, to liberate the people from min's reign, finally defeating min in a dramatic, bloody battle, or you can do what nobody else does. Sit when he says sit, and beat the game in 5 minutes. I suggest the bloody option, More guns, and explosions. We all love explosions.", "timestamp_created": 1421971323, "timestamp_updated": 1421971323, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "14045697", "author": {"steamid": "76561198022320677", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 24, "playtime_forever": 11627, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 4912, "last_played": 1737261015}, "language": "english", "review": "Not sure about this one. Would say i deffinitly got my moneys worth out of it in hours. Did not like the characters or the cut scenes, they quickly started to drag on. Did not enjoy the story line quests either. Only worth in this game is the claiming of the towers and outposts which is the same as farcry 3 but a new map. The grapple climbing is very well done but the forcing of long quests without weapons that you spent hours unlocking seems pointless. There are still errors with the mechanics, like opening of the wing suit and jumping over walls. Worst of all is the Shangri-la quests, on hardmode there is almost no possible plan attack its just sloppy arcade style with respawning bad guys.

I read a review saying some things similar to what i have said here before i got the game. After getting it i had a few moments where i thought this is awesome. Not most is done i am bored as with it. Dont think i would replay once i get to 100% and the only parts left are the slow collecting of bits that simply remind me of GTA collections, not very fun. 

Final note, the arena is most cool and probably best part of the game. for $75 you will get your money worth but could have had more work, or work put into better areas of the game.", "timestamp_created": 1421568383, "timestamp_updated": 1421568383, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "14003365", "author": {"steamid": "76561197978069247", "num_games_owned": 533, "num_reviews": 142, "playtime_forever": 3821, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2621, "last_played": 1702607456}, "language": "english", "review": "Far Cry 4 is basically Far Cry 3 with a new story on top; you still capture towers and outposts. Gameplay mechanics are almost verbatim. If you liked FC3, then you should be able to enjoy FC4. I enjoyed both games but grew tired of the mechanics by the end of FC4.

As FC3 was graphically demanding, FC4 is more graphically demanding. I only started playing after the 1.6 patch and I've not experienced any bad hitching. You will need to take into consideration that you may not be able to crank up all details and get a smooth experience, so drop details until you can maintain your desired frame rate. FC4 is very pretty, though, and that's what really kept me going. I ran it with a Galaxy GTX 780 HOF with an overclock on the RAM, which helps quite a bit; FC4 loves to use everything it can. The graphics are very nice, so it's definitely not just wasting energy on the GPU.

I recommend Far Cry 4, but consider that it is very similar to Far Cry 3 and judge for yourself what that is worth to you.", "timestamp_created": 1421370508, "timestamp_updated": 1421370508, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 91, "votes_funny": 11, "weighted_vote_score": "0.736000955104827881", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13996869", "author": {"steamid": "76561198015530522", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 13, "playtime_forever": 11145, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 9726, "last_played": 1463599181}, "language": "english", "review": "This is an ultimate sandbox game experience, but with a clear objective. The clarity is defined by YOU, the gamer, as you gain insight in whats going on in this ancient region. Your insights will guide you in the path you are about to take; A path that only can be walked, not told. Be aware! Your path is affected by an ongoing conflict and there is more than one thing that will try to end you, either by default or because of your doing. 

This game is a rewarding experience, and the difficulty is kept on an ever increasing level to keep you on your toes. But you also gain rewards and cash to buy better things to carry with you to survive. To beat the game, you have to play for a long time. However, if you stick to the storyline, the campain can be finished in an tolerable time. 

