{"recommendationid": "13577845", "author": {"steamid": "76561197960271686", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 3, "playtime_forever": 4314, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 3500, "last_played": 1539393599}, "language": "english", "review": "Overall, this game is just ok. The graphics are just ok, the combat is just ok, the story is just ok. 

Unfortunately, while it does nothing really well, it does quite a few things poorly: Cutscenes are unskippable, and if you fail or die on a mission you'll have to repeat them. AI (human and animal) is hilariously bad. Random karma events are annoying. The first hang-glider you get in the starting town is placed such that it unavoidably hits a tree immediately upon launch. Press and hold "e" to do do anything, then lose control and wait through an overly dramatic 2-3 second animation to complete before regaining control. This was so irritating that, once when the game skipped these animations because there was not enough room, I was really unbelievably happy. Grappling and climbing can only be done in predefined positions, all of which are very conveniently located and are all indicated by the same pile of very convenient ropes. This makes scaling towers so tedious that it's much more fun to just land a helicopter inside the top of the tower. You can do that of course, because the rotor hit detection is virtually non-existant.  Carefully aimed sniper bullets and arrows sometimes go right through a target without any explanation, while other times, enemies will die after spraying bullets vaugely in their direction. Graphics are nothing special - flying over mountain vistas should elicit some sense of awe. Instead you just realise how low res the heightmap and terrain textures are, and how out of place the static rock and mountain assets look. Despite a relatively beefy system, LOD pop-in happens all the time. What makes this worse is that it is implemented by fading in high-poly models with this weird dissolving effect. Unfortunately it happens so often and at such short distances that it's just annoying.

Good things: Big game hunting endangered animals with a mounted machine gun so I can use their skins to make a new wallet. Riding an elephant and making it kick another elephant in the butt.", "timestamp_created": 1419460545, "timestamp_updated": 1521850837, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.484477579593658447", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

