{"recommendationid": "13400991", "author": {"steamid": "76561198063281813", "num_games_owned": 194, "num_reviews": 84, "playtime_forever": 2188, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2188, "last_played": 1418307235}, "language": "english", "review": "Far Cry 4 was pretty fun. It captured all the open world freedom and country liberating mayhem that you had in the previous instalment and it throws it into a new Himalayan setting with a few new cool skills and twists.

Overall the story wasn't very complex but they do throw you a few curveballs by the end. The villain Pagan Min is probably the only likable character in the game, and unfortunately you don't interact with him all too much until the later portions of the game. Besides this however, the game plays great. You feel like an absolute bad ass once you unlock a few of the skills, and you can use many different tactics to take on any situation. The game gives you a few memorable set pieces such as driving a quad bike off a cliff-side runway, using your wingsuit to catch up to a plane that just took off, and then opening the door and throwing a grenade inside! Awesome stuff!

