{"recommendationid": "13381881", "author": {"steamid": "76561198097679879", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 51, "playtime_forever": 9642, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 8667, "last_played": 1737101419}, "language": "english", "review": "This is my first Far Cry game, I know the plot of the 3rd, and that's it, I picked this one up a couple of weeks after the release, amazing graphics, great not AMAZING plot, perfect stealth fundimentals, likeable characters, you can make choices that affect the plot substantially, there are about 11 different endings I believe, and if you like me really care what stealth takedown animations look like, you will be pleasently suprised as your character shoves a machate into you enemies neck then pull the pin from a gernade and kick the body into a group of people, blowing all of them up. Highly recommended, I got the $90 version of the game, and let me just say I would pay twice as much, this game is truly a masterpiece, so much so, that I went back and bought the Far Cry 3 on steam, and it is currently downloading. The map is gigantic, great handeling, great controls which are customizable by the way, always animations, even for small things like opening doors. I finished this GIGANTIC game in just a week while I was sick at home. COMPLETLY RECOMMENDED!

That was the first draft which I wrote about a year ago. This is going to be me looking back on it after a year of dissapointment in games (not all games). This game is the best first single player first person shooter created in the last 6 years. I've looked back and there are some amazing games but this is just perfection. It gives you a feeling like you're actually the protagonist of this game. You ARE Ajay Ghale and it's YOUR mission to save the country of Kyrat and give your familes name honor again. YOU're the person blowing up huge statues and shooting down hundreds of people from a helicopter while awesome badass music is playing. No other single player first person shooter has given me this feeling. I would pay twice the amount I did for this game. It's so ammersive you forget you're sitting there in your chair in front of the computer like the loner you are. You become the main character, you choose the destiny of a country, and you blow shit up! GET THIS GAME!

I'm writing this one like years later, once more. I'm now much much much less pasionate about games and don't really care. I remember this game so well, and when I recently went back and played it, it didn't dissapoint. It didn't give me the same feeling it did the first time, but that's because I was 4 years younger and it was one of the first games I had ever played that I didn't first watch a walkthrough of by a youtuber. Looking back, it's still a solid game. Good gunplay, good stealth, good voice acting, good animation, good map, good story, good everything. Is it like as amazing as I sold it as? Nah probably not. Is it the best first person shooter of the past 6 years? Nah probably not. But it's still really good. I'm writing this before playing 5 which looks kinda ok. If it sounds like I'm not excited, it's because I'm not. Whatevs, let's see what 5 offers.", "timestamp_created": 1418671995, "timestamp_updated": 1522471126, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 4, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.580566585063934326", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

