{"recommendationid": "13372829", "author": {"steamid": "76561197984347587", "num_games_owned": 440, "num_reviews": 19, "playtime_forever": 2091, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2007, "last_played": 1418786744}, "language": "english", "review": "Just beat the game with all the towers and outposts complete. It took a good chunk of time to do so, around 34 hours, so I'm happy that it's as long as it is if you do the side stuff. If you blaze through just the campaign missions it'll feel quite short. But anyways, did you like Far Cry 3? Do you want more of that? Cool, play this game, you'll love it. Because of a few certain weapons, the game can tend to be a bit easy, especially once you get around to getting the small explosives launcher, and a silenced sniper rifle, but that's how Far Cry 3 was too. Outposts are fun to take out, Radio towers are fun to climb, the Shangri-Lah stuff is a good change of pace and visually very pretty.

The buzzer though, the one-man copter, kinda makes the Radio Towers too easy seeing as how you can just land the damn thing on the top floor of most of them and complete them that way. The buzzer makes quite a few things very easy actually, so maybe make a decision to not use it for things to up the difficulty a bit.

Games fun. I really enjoyed Far Cry 3, and this is just more of that and since it's been long enough since I personally played Far Cry 3, I'm all for it. If Far Cry 5 is just this again though... eh I'll probably still enjoy it. Wonder how many iterations it'll take before it gets old though.", "timestamp_created": 1418610853, "timestamp_updated": 1418610964, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

