{"recommendationid": "13091051", "author": {"steamid": "76561198031031254", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 16, "playtime_forever": 6172, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 4149, "last_played": 1447125269}, "language": "english", "review": "If you enjoyed Far Cry 3 then you will enjoy 4. I have the Nvidia GeForce GTX 780 Ti video card and did not experience any of the technical problems some users reported on release day. The game plays just like 3, just think of it as new content. Which is not a bad thing to me. Some people complained its the same game mechanics as the previous game. So what? If it isn't broke why fix it? Graphics are good, no complaint there. Ive noticed a few minor glitches in the game but that's when Ive been playing a solid 8+ hours and a simple exit and restart fixed it.

