The game has a few issues performance wise. these can be, for the most part, suppressed. In the graphical settings I recomend setting SHADOWS to HIGH, AA to SMAA, AMBIENT OCCLUSION to SSBC, TREES RELIEF to OFF, and maybe GEOMETERY to VERY HIGH/HIGH. also try these in GamerProfile.xml: DisableLoadingMip0="1" (I don't use this because of texture degredation) , AlphaToCoverage="0" (barely noticable in-game and gives a pretty good FPS boost), and GPUMaxBufferedFrames="3" (this should help with stuttering). With these settings and a 280x the game is stable and looks almost identical to Maxed settings. I hope this will help some people with performance.", "timestamp_created": 1416718258, "timestamp_updated": 1416718258, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

