{"recommendationid": "13010739", "author": {"steamid": "76561198019541920", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 17178, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 822, "last_played": 1425184204}, "language": "english", "review": "If you are expecting something entirely different from Far Cry 3 (which a lot of these reviewers seem to be) then you will be sadly disappointed. It's honestly a lot like FC3. The mechanics are the same, animations of skinning and picking leaves are the same, and the whole idea of liberating camps is the same. And you know what? It's still an effing BLAST! I am so overwhelmed with things to do and goals to meet. 

My husband and I have been playing co-op all day and I have to say, I have never played such a fun and rewarding co-op game. We have been hunting and upgrading our gear, liberating posts, opening up the map together. It's all been great. Minor glitches such as he cannot see vehicles on the road and sometimes he dies from one bite of a honey badger (that HAS to be a glitch, right?). 

Point blank -- it's a Far Cry game. They decided to stick with the same mechanics of the last Far Cry game probably because of its success. If you're looking for something brand new and groundbreaking don't bother. If you want do play Far Cry again with some new stuff (entirely new story and map, new characters, new adventures, new animals, co-op) then please give it a shot. You won't be disappointed. I have played Far Cry 1-4 now and loved them all.", "timestamp_created": 1416440364, "timestamp_updated": 1416440364, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 7, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.526687502861022949", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

